story_txt:
Considering the overwhelmingly positive response to the black and white edition of Cupid's Farewell Christmas, we are thrilled and grateful that our quirky holiday tale about daring to be yourself has already touched so many people.We believe this funny, fresh take on Christmas—one that resonates with people of all ages and backgrounds—should be delivered, in its fully realized vision, to people grown tired of recycled stories and the hyper-commercialization of one of the world's most cherished holidays.Our goal is simple: to transform the illustrations from the black and white 2017 edition into full color and deliver a finished book that becomes an enduring holiday season classic. The first edition, black and white version of Cupid's Farewell Christmas has nearly 60 illustrations, the majority of which still need to be completed to make the full-color 2018 edition available for widespread distribution next holiday season.The artistic standards that we have set for the project are high, and the vision for the final book is as a keepsake gift of the utmost quality: one that may be read, shared, and enjoyed year after year.Our goal for this stage of the project is to raise $5,000, the majority of which will be used to support Sonny as he completes the colorization of the original images from the black and white edition of the book.The other funds will be dedicated to optimizing our social media campaign, Indiegogo fees, and all of the perks that a happy Santa will deliver to all of those supporters on his Nice List. The colorization of the first edition illustrations will be digital, and each image will require a similar degree of attention so that each one evokes the nostalgia of a classic painting, like the book's cover. Considering this, the greatest challenge to having a full-color book ready for publication and widespread distribution in 2018 is adequate time and funding. Unlike the two-year rendering of the black and white edition, however, coloring the original illustrations of Cupid's Farewell Christmas will require approximately 3-4 months of focused, dedicated work. With sufficient funding, the illustrator, Sonny Quinn, is committed to the time required and eager to complete the project. 181 years delivering toys has Santa Claus ready to call it quits. He’s burnt-out, saddled with hemorrhoids, and needs to carry a shotgun to do the dangerous business of climbing down chimneys. In fact, Santa's ready to quit “this wicked-bitch of a route” and retire somewhere warm, like Boca Raton, or Las Vegas.Santa’s troubles only magnify when his favorite reindeer—the beloved, but rebellious Cupid—runs off on Christmas Eve.Now facing a world on edge and a runaway reindeer, what's a not-so-jolly Saint Nick to do on what just might be his last Christmas? The gifts and perks for getting on Santa's Nice List and supporting Cupid's Farewell Christmas include:
Personalized animated holiday eCard from Evan & Quinn;
Signed first edition copies of Cupid's Farewell Christmas;
Signed and personalized first edition copies of Cupid's Farewell Christmas;
Signed and personalized full-color copies of Cupid's Farewell Christmas;
"Santa's Bagged" tote bags;
5-packs of "It always feels best when we give" Humping Reindeer Christmas cards;
"Humping Reindeer" Christmas tree ornaments;
Contributor's name(s) featured on the 2018 edition "Acknowledgments" page;
Signed and framed 12"x18" prints of "Santa's gotta do what he's gotta do;"
Original art: Signed and framed original concept sketches;
Two original paintings;
And more.
The creative team, Cliff Evan & Sonny Quinn, are both graduates from Columbia University's School of the Arts.The author, Clifford Evan, is a freelance writer and college instructor whose novel Delivered was released in paperback in 2013.The illustrator, Sonny Quinn, is a painter, a storyboard artist, and the director of the documentary film A Light in the Dark, the Art and Life of Frank Mason, an official selection of the Newport Beach and Big Apple Film Festivals. Santa is, well…Santa. The greatest challenge to having full color book ready for publication and widespread distribution in 2018 is adequate time and funding. Unlike the two-year rendering of the black and white edition, however, coloring the original illustrations of Cupid's Farewell Christmas will require approximately 3-4 months of focused, dedicated work. With sufficient funding, the illustrator Sonny Quinn is committed to the time required and eager to complete the project.Original art takes time to complete. Many of the world's most famous and beloved illustrated books, first rendered as original paintings, have taken years to produce. The black and white illustrations for Cupid's Farewell Christmas were each hand-drawn in pencil before being digitally revised. That was the most challenging stage of the project. and took nearly two years to go from the roughest of sketches to the published first edition. We anticipate that it will take Sonny 3-4 months to color these original illustrations. Getting funded now, though, will give us the opportunity to get you a black and white version for this Christmas and then the full-color edition for next year! Even if you cannot contribute financially to Cupid's Farewell Christmas, you can still help us to reach our project goals of making the book a new holiday classic by spreading the holiday cheer and letting your friends and family know about our campaign on social media. Just a couple of clicks and shares on Indiegogo will get you right onto Santa's Nice List!Thank you and silver bells of holiday cheer to all!Clifford Evan & Sonny Quinn
